content.description: There's a couple of nice big holds at first, but the rest is crimps.
content.location: Start at the chalky shelf inside the hole, then make your way straight up.
This route is found on the north side of the key hole boulders.

content.description: make sure to check the bird's nest that is at the start for any birds or snakes or what have you before beginning.
content.location: This route is found on the north west side of the Key Hole Hole Boulders, start at the shelf that has a bird's nest inside a hole in it.  Then make your way to the top by following the crack.

content.description: Fun little warm-up route, make sure to check for spiders and snakes before starting.  You know, usual Nevada stuff.
content.location: The start of this route is just below the "2002" grafitti.  Follow the chalk marks along the crack to the left and over the top.

content.description: almost nothing but finger pockets, short problem.
content.location: On the west side of the Key Hole Boulders.  If you crawl through the key hole, the route will be around the corner to the left.  Start at the undercling on the bottom, then follow the finger pockets to the top.

content.description: Volcanic rock, looks like the rest of the Washoe Boulders. The shady north east side has a couple routes in and around the hole through the center of these two boulders. More routes can be found on the west, northwest, and northern side of these boulders. Can’t find info on this chunk of rock anywhere else online, but there are some pretty well chalked routes on them already, so it’ll probably pop up in a guide book with a different name. More to come on that.
